
GitHub Side
Setup your github pages site

Jekyll Side
Install Jekyll
Add the necessary files (Build.R, BuildOne.R .rprofile) - Can use the knitr-jekyll theme from yihui
Customize your theme (DIY or find one)

R Side
Install Blogdown, knitr, servr

Add Source .RMD files to _source
run servr::jekyll() to knit the files to .md and automatically add to _posts. 

Done.